commit_message:
Use SSHManager instead of context manager
 - Function update_connection was added in SSHManager.
   You can use it to update existed connecetion with
   new/custom credentials

 - Function execute_on_remote was renamed to 'execut'
 - Function execute_on_remote was added to SSHManager
   with new functionality. It is the same with
   run_on_remote_and_get_result
 - Move function json_deserialize to SSHManager
 - Code refactoring according the changes above

 SSHManager was added in folowing places:
  - fuelweb_test.environment.py for all needed methods
  - patching.py for:
     - connect_admin_to_repo
     - connect_slaves_to_repo
  - decorators.py for update_rpm_packages
  - multiple_networks_hacks.py for all
Related-Bug: #1527847

Change-Id: I20dd5e02bb8833b3543780e0083576516a2893f6

commit_message:
Create separate non-dvr router for baremetal when Neutron DVR enabled

DVR is not working with Ironic yet, so when DVR is enabled in cluster
baremetal servers should use separate non-distributed router.

Partial-bug: #1523878

commit_message:
Improve reliability of fence_ssh reboots

- Added ServerAliveInterval 2 SSH option
- Modified reboot command to run forked
- Reboot now is an ungraceful forced reboot
- Reboot now runs with no stdin, stdout, stderr in order
  to reduce the chance of leaked FDs slowing down reboot

Change-Id: Ie35b9e40e4c38bc547efbaaf3be44f84538fc626
Closes-Bug: #1528574

commit_message:
Add validation for templates_for_node_role

Add check for templates for node role in network template.
All nodes roles existing in cluster should be present in network template.
If it is not true InvalidData exception will be raised.

Change-Id: I6be3c115b59d9f0a17074995d4cea88b31f53ae1
Closes-Bug: #1490536

commit_message:
Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method in favor of warning

Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method, see:
https://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.html#logging.warning, so we
prefer to use warning to avoid DeprecationWarning.

Change-Id: Ief3c6c16ff5d9f6236ca845dceed2534d84457f4

commit_message:
Hardcoded parent keys removed from fixtures

Changes:

- field 'pk' removed from fixtures,
- algorithm of checking fixture presence in DB changed. now we are using
  'identify_fields' fixture field with DB model properties names for
  searching object in the DB instead hardcoded 'pk' value,
- filtration of loading fixtures by presence 'pk' in them removed,
- fixture field 'save_to_db' used for explicitly marking is fixture must
  be saved or not. by default we assume fixture must be saved to the DB,
- field 'children' added to fixtures for adding dependable fixtures.
  related to the parent property must be in the child fixture 'fields',
- fixman slightly refactored. several private functions decoupled from
  upload_fixture function.
- pending fixtures workflow removed from upload_fixture function. children
  fixtures feature covers this workflow
- dump fixture action in manage.py fixed

Change-Id: Ibcdbf55d16eb7d947058ba4ea68f692ad45b09a2
Closes-Bug: #1526917
Closes-Bug: #1528620

commit_message:
No More Downward SQL Schema Migrations

From OpenStack spec[1], SQL Migrations are the accepted method for
OpenStack projects to ensure that a given schema is consistent across
deployments. Often these migrations include updating of the underlying
data as well as modifications to the schema. It is inadvisable to
perform a downwards migration in any environment.
We should eliminate db downgrade methods in Manila as suggestion and
as the other OpenStack projects do.

http://specs.openstack.org/openstack/openstack-specs/specs/
no-downward-sql-migration.html

Change-Id: Ifd942338e954dcbc5dea9f995deb71e549a2a8c9
Closes-Bug: #1525479

commit_message:
Actions directive should take Service

Currently the actions directive uses callbacks and
permissions to determine what actions are allowed
and what callback to bind them.

The callback is passed as strings which result in
leaky abstractions and implicit binding of the
controller and the service with the HTML.

The patch changes the directive to only require a service
which needs to provide functions that help the directive
determine if the action is permitted and what method
to call when the action is performed.

Change-Id: I91f009c10c5db8bf0b0082625b259bf1ba7358c3
Partially-Implements: blueprint angularize-images-table

subject: Raise exception when failed to get discovery_url
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-12-28 01:20:24.000000000', 'files': ['magnum/conductor/template_definition.py', 'magnum/tests/unit/conductor/test_template_definition.py', 'magnum/common/exception.py'], 'message': 'Raise exception when failed to get discovery_url

If discovery endpoint is not accessible, magnum returns "ERROR: Timed
out waiting for a reply to message ID a74fe7ec63b34f298c46c9f6659257d7
(HTTP 500)" when we create a bay. The response is misleading.
So we should raise exception when magnum fails to get discovery_url
and make the response easy to understand.

commit_message:
Raise exception when failed to get discovery_url

If discovery endpoint is not accessible, magnum returns "ERROR: Timed
out waiting for a reply to message ID a74fe7ec63b34f298c46c9f6659257d7
(HTTP 500)" when we create a bay. The response is misleading.
So we should raise exception when magnum fails to get discovery_url
and make the response easy to understand.

Change-Id: Ia649e55de0878160f42fecf1647d9da7fc954d72
Closes-Bug: #1529200

commit_message:
Remove references to _i18n and apiclient.exceptions

Since oslo-incubator is no longer maintained[1] after
90ae25e38915cc502d9e9c52d59e8fb668a72ae1. We should cleanup
the deprecated code.

This patch do the following cleanup actions:
1. Use magnumclient.i18n instead of
magnumclient.openstack.common._i18n.
2. Use magnumclient.exceptions instead of the deprecated
magnumclient.openstack.common.apiclient.exceptions[2].

[1] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-November/
    079343.html

commit_message:
Enable TLS in loadbalancer if cert path is detected

If there is a value for the certificate path (which should only happen
if the environment for enabling TLS is used) then the loadbalancer will
detect it and configure it's front ends correctly. On the other hand
a proper override for the example environment was given, since this
will be needed because we want to pass the hosts and protocols
correctly so the tripleoclient will catch it and pass it to
os-cloud-config

Change-Id: Ifba51495f0c99398291cfd29d10c04ec33b8fc34
Depends-On: Ie2428093b270ab8bc19fcb2130bb16a41ca0ce09

commit_message:
outlet Temperature based migration strategy

It implements one of the algorithm of Intel thermal POC.
It extends the BaseStrategy class, getting the Outlet
metrics of servers via Ceilometer, and generates solutions
when the outlet Temperature is greater than threshold.
current threshold is hard-coded, will make it configurable
in the next patches.

Implements: blueprint outlet-temperature-based-strategy

Change-Id: I248147329d34eddf408652205a077895be572010
Co-Authored-By: Zhenzan Zhou <zhenzan.zhou@intel.com>

commit_message:
Put py34 first in the env order of tox

To solve the problem of "db type could
not be determined" on py34 we have to run first the py34 env to, then, run
py27. This patch puts py34 first on the tox.ini list of envs to avoid this
problem to happen.

Closes-bug: #1489059

commit_message:
Add pip-check-reqs tox environment

This change adds a new tox environment 'pip-check-reqs'. This env
will test for requirements that are imported in source files but
are missing from requirements.txt as well as finding modules in
requirements.txt that are never imported/used by the project.

This requires a new venv as we can't polute it with
test-requirements.txt or itself.

This change also includes the fixes to requirements.txt needed
to pass the new tests.

Change-Id: Iee91b46638121947c30f1a0887a3230eef085d04

commit_message:
Add pip-check-reqs tox environment

This change adds a new tox environment 'pip-check-reqs'. This env
will test for requirements that are imported in source files but
are missing from requirements.txt as well as finding modules in
requirements.txt that are never imported/used by the project.

This requires a new venv as we can't polute it with
test-requirements.txt or itself.

This change also includes the fixes to requirements.txt needed
to pass the new tests.

commit_message:
Fix pip install settings

There were some inconsistencies with pip install instructions
thoughout Kolla. We fix those here.

Additionally, we fix the virtualenv to properly use the site-packages
on the host if a library is not available in the venv.

Change-Id: Ib84d48e8826bb96060338b3fa0782620c98794a8
Related-Bug: #1524684
Closes-Bug: #1529434

commit_message:
Adjust CMD for data and kolla-ansible

The CMD command for data causes docker to launch it with /bin/sh which
is ugly when viewing the containers statuses. Additionally for
kolla_ansible we were not specifying the CMD at all, forcing us to use
the 'command' param to set the sleep command.

This patch brings the kolla_ansible launch inline with the rest of the
project.

TrivialFix

Change-Id: Ic87a89921674802c15596756526e07f52a782f32

commit_message:
Remove the deprecated ibmnas driver

The ibmnas driver has been deprecated since the Liberty release.
In the Liberty release, NFS capabilities were added to the IBM
GPFS driver with commit:  bf4ca3bcf099760ef145571b975badc80d42b2d6 .
The ability for the GPFS driver to use NFS based shares rendered
the ibmnas driver redundant.

This commit removes the ibmnas driver and its tests.  The commit also
updates the opts.py file to remove reference to the ibmnas options.

Release notes are included with this commit.

DocImpact

Change-Id: Iac4a2f1770f7d02979eec1d8d5866d9fc4b6d18c

commit_message:
Updated violin driver check for volume objects

Fixed bug where both vmem 6000 drivers were trying to export luns as
snapshots when using the base volume driver's copy_volume_data()
function.

Bug was observed during recent CI runs.

Closes-Bug: 1517240

commit_message:
Making NFS _find_share efficient

NfsDriver's _find_share calls self._is_share_eligible, which calls
get_capacity_info(). Then, it calls get_capacity_info() itself.

The method is optimized to not call underlying get_capacity_info()
twice.

Change-Id: I07a0601b9d902e54f84540f05cdadd5587522643
Closes-Bug: #1507682

of heat engine. It should help users to understand
which resource is need to.

 * magnum
 * mistral

commit_message:
Update connection strings for other services

This change continues the improvement of using the db_connection_string
function to generate connection strings for the services.  This change
updates the heat, ironic, murano, cinder, neutron and sahara to use the
generated connection strings instead.

Change-Id: I3b889c9035c57b872ba6eeab811ddec25cc4c330
Closes-Bug: #1526938

Currently, CinderObjectDictCompat.get will default to None if a field
is not in the object, however if a field is present in the object
but the value is not yet set we get an error instead of None. To be
consistent with dict.get() we should default to None if the field
is not present or not set.

Change-Id: Id87efeaaeb2fb44960d8d0df9aa854dd156bff45
'}]
commit_message:
Modify VO so that obj.get always defaults to None

Currently, CinderObjectDictCompat.get will default to None if a field
is not in the object, however if a field is present in the object
but the value is not yet set we get an error instead of None. To be
consistent with dict.get() we should default to None if the field
is not present or not set.

Change-Id: Id87efeaaeb2fb44960d8d0df9aa854dd156bff45

commit_message:
py26 is no longer supported by Infra's CI

Python 2.6 support would be dropped by

Put py34 first in the env order of tox

To solve the problem of "db type could not be determined" we have to run
first the py34 env and then py2x. This patch puts py34 first on the
tox.ini list of envs to avoid this problem.

commit_message:
Drop (v)2.0 from FWaaS and VPNaaS APIs

FWaaS and VPNaaS API have no so-call v2.0 API.
They are just part of Networking v2.0 API.
Thus FWaaS v2.0a and VPNaaS 2.0 API make no sense.

Change-Id: I869f5789d1f823446b7f024a5e1f91522ec7720a
Closes-Bug: #1529368

commit_message:
Syntax error fixed: 'mysql'.'user' ->  mysql.user

The command "GRANT SELECT ON 'mysql'.'user' TO ..." has an syntax
error. It should be either `mysql`.`user` or just mysql.user.
For consistency, this commit changes to just mysql.user
with appropriate mysql code block instead of console code block.

Co-Authored-By: KATO Tomoyuki <kato.tomoyuki@jp.fujitsu.com>
Change-Id: I5523db35cd68eb985069baab648b67998e46f919
Closes-Bug: #1518384

Change-Id: I1e85537d137a1b773198facbb835a65b6d0ce9b4

commit_message:
Tox: Remove fullstack env, keep only dsvm-fullstack

In the functional tests we have 'functional' and 'dsvm-functional'
venvs. The difference is that dsvm-functional requires can run
rootwrap commands on the machine. In the fullstack context,
not running rootwrap commands doesn't make sense, as fullstack
tests are explicitly and solely integration tests.

Change-Id: I1e85537d137a1b773198facbb835a65b6d0ce9b4
(cherry picked from commit dd5a8e41669b965f8c1244c67a54f81e11efe3c2)

commit_message:
use keystoneclient exceptions instead of oslo-incubator code

depending on any oslo-incubator code from another project is
dangerous. keystoneclient makes its exceptions public and it's
not recommended to use any code from
keystoneclient.openstack.common.apiclient since it's maintained
by oslo-incubator.

Fix dependencies for cinder-block-device role

commit_message:
Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method in favor of warning

Python 3 deprecated the logger.warn method, see:
https://docs.python.org/3/library/logging.html#logging.warning, so we
prefer to use warning to avoid DeprecationWarning.

Change-Id: Icde5ec3809383f33dd56d5a76b25ff5021598d5d

commit_message:
Add config option to enable reporting discard

The way for a client of Cinder (read: Nova) to know whether or not it
can and should use the discard feature for the block device attachment
is to report back discard=True in the connection info. Previously a
driver would need to be updated to provide this functionality, which is
kind of a pain with so many drivers in Cinder.

This change adds a shared boolean config option called
‘report_discard_supported’ which can be set to enable reporting this
functionality to the caller of initialize_connection.

DocImpact
Change-Id: I078e74583621316bcfe138096507e7d22af0d712
Implements: blueprint discard-config-option

commit_message:
Pass fuel-bootstrap-cli config to containers

* install fuel-bootstrap-cli in mcollective bootstrap
* we need rw permission for successful package
  install\upgrade inside container (linked config file will not be changed -
  new one will be saved with .rpmnew)

Change-Id: I7b2a096cec99ec5923b00f6b084987455adf0637

This Patch enables this tests for all new patches to tacker.

F402 import module shadowed by loop variable
F812 list comprehension redefines name from line

see OpenStack Style Guidelines

This patch cleans up py26 and py33 references,

commit_message:
use keystoneclient exceptions instead of oslo-incubator code

depending on any oslo-incubator code from another project is
dangerous. keystoneclient makes its exceptions public and it's
not recommended to use any code from
keystoneclient.openstack.common.apiclient since it's maintained
by oslo-incubator.

commit_message:
[Reports] Add abstract class Table class and improve MainStatsTable

This is about upcoming changes output format - new class
OutputStatsTable will be added soon, so existing code is reworked
to become more unified and flexible:

  * abstract class `Table' is added - it is a base for
    MainStatsTable, and it will be a base for upcoming
    OutputStatsTable as well
  * redundant variables self.rows and self.rows_index
    are replaced with already available Chart._data
  * columns list is moved to property COLUMNS
  * common logic is moved to new method get_rows()
  * new method _row_has_results() is added to make it
    flexible for subclasses to check if row is effective
  * implicit changes are replaced with explicit

Change-Id: I4ce12a2a0b78304949956aa58837397ec49a1962
Implements: spec improve_scenario_output_format.rst

commit_message:
Improve output for "os security group show"

Improve the security group rules output when running the
"os security group show" command. Each security group rule
is now displayed on a separate line.

Current output example:
$ openstack security group show default
+-------------+------------------------- ... ---+
| Field       | Value                    ...    |
+-------------+------------------------- ... ---+
| description | Default security group   ...    |
| id          | 048a5fc3-3be1-407d-ae47-9...    |
| name        | default                  ...    |
| project_id  | 3b96bb2020c1459da76963f9e...    |
| rules       | [u"id='5d812367-9829-4340...t"] |
+-------------+------------------------- ... ---+

New output example:
+-------------+------------------------- ... ---+
| Field       | Value                    ...    |
+-------------+------------------------- ... ---+
| description | Default security group   ...    |
| id          | 048a5fc3-3be1-407d-ae47-9...    |
| name        | default                  ...    |
| project_id  | 3b96bb2020c1459da76963f9e...    |
| rules       | id='5d812367-9829-4340-95...lt' |
|             | id='ee451d1c-ade3-4975-8e...lt' |
+-------------+------------------------- ... ---+

Change-Id: I1386075310896c58a2b776e2bbec3603bd00eff1
Partial-Bug: #1519511
Related-To: blueprint neutron-client

[{'number': 4, 'created': '2015-12-21 13:44:15.000000000', 'files': ['files/fuel-ha-utils/ocf/rabbitmq'], 'message': 'Don't update .erlang.cookie on every run

Update happens even during no-op commands like 'meta-data' or 'usage'.
During this update there is a short window for a race condition: a shell
redirection truncates the cookie file, and echo writes data there only
after a brief period of time. So erlang may read data from this empty
file and die with error "Too short cookie string".

Change-Id: I4c3201617669f3872145048b77337632cb93558c
Closes-Bug: #1512754
(cherry picked from commit 8e1bfe6f5c8994800200b0670ab8d4820d9f8c2e)
'}]
commit_message:
Don't update .erlang.cookie on every run

Update happens even during no-op commands like 'meta-data' or 'usage'.
During this update there is a short window for a race condition: a shell
redirection truncates the cookie file, and echo writes data there only
after a brief period of time. So erlang may read data from this empty
file and die with error "Too short cookie string".

Change-Id: I4c3201617669f3872145048b77337632cb93558c
Closes-Bug: #1512754
(cherry picked from commit 8e1bfe6f5c8994800200b0670ab8d4820d9f8c2e)

This commit introduced patch that breaks the Dragonflow
pipeline installation.
Need to investigate why this breaks the pipeline but right
now i dont see why there should be sync problem, we can
solve it with a semaphore in the mean time however
different threads shouldnt try to update the same

commit_message:
Workaround for detection of CentOS NVMe disks added

On CentOs udevadm returns the same ids for NVMe disks.
For handling this case we use matched by name devices.

Partial-Bug: #1503987

revisions:

Python time.sleep() can't be interrupted. We have our own interruptable
realization of this method. It should be used instead of time.sleep() at
least in common methods for rally code such as task.scenario.sleep_between.

Change-Id: I8b77bc819e3ca5ee43a4bbda7cd131879dc651fe
"}]
commit_message:
Use interruptable sleep in sleep_between method

Python time.sleep() can't be interrupted. We have our own interruptable
realization of this method. It should be used instead of time.sleep() at
least in common methods for rally code such as task.scenario.sleep_between.

Change-Id: I8b77bc819e3ca5ee43a4bbda7cd131879dc651fe

commit_message:
Refresh nailgun systemd units if settings.yaml is updated

This was caused by starting systemd services before applying
Puppet, which prevented Puppet changes to settings from taking
effect immediately.

commit_message:
Functional tests: remove references to environment

The functional tests had references to environment
variable, eg os.environ.get('OS_USERNAME').

Since tox 2.0 environment variables are not passed
through to the tests, so it makes sense to remove
references to them.

Change-Id: Ib72fc5e35bd539f02647c9f0eb5a937cc409e433

commit_message:
Remove import_from_format in Task input

Currently, we don't use import_from_format provided in the task_
input and it's a mandatory property. It's better to remove the
field and add it when an use-case arises.

This will not break the v2 tasks api and is backwards compatible
since we are only removing a field that was never used.

Change-Id: If1847ff92d483546e829fe5471785ad366d942bc

commit_message:
Support image list for deleted images

Now when talking about deleted images in Glance, there are two
aspects: status and deleted fields from database view.

For v2, now it's harded code to hide the deleted images. This patch
will enable the 'status' filter so that end user can list deleted
images with status=<status>.

Closes-Bug: #1432701

Change-Id: I7fced3d8d037aef8e11b402366a3fbc3cc8527a3

commit_message:
Functional tests for metadata seeding for glance-manage

Currently there are no functional tests for metadata seeding for
glance-manage. This tests should cover a specific lifecycle of metadata
using three api methods:

db_load_metadefs
db_unload_metadefs
db_export_metadefs

This change set does not cover metadef upgrades.

Co-Authored-By: Bartosz Fic <bartosz.fic@intel.com>
Co-Authored-By: Pawel Koniszewski <pawel.koniszewski@intel.com>
Change-Id: Ia288ec5e79487557166384f857b629c5e58f11f4
Partial-Bug: #1373936

commit_message:
Use more accurate message in glance v2 api

glance v2 api uses multiple proxies, the exceptions are thrown from
those proxies and be handled in v2 api. The original message in
exception is more accurate, we should show that original message to
user, instead of making a common message which is not useful for
end user. For example: when user attempts to create membership to
a public image, currently he will get a message "Not allowed to
create members for image", user doesn't get useful information.
If we use the message from the original exception, it will show
"Public images do not have members", it is more accurate.

Closes-Bug: #1469356

Change-Id: Ifef05ed2eeb279c61fdbf6b777effae502f708f1

commit_message:
Delete image in case of import tasks failure

If the import flow fails due to any reason, the partially
created image is stuck in queuing/saving state. This patch deletes
the image and the cleans up the uploaded chunks.

In order to execute the revert methods of all tasks in the flow,
the taskflow revert strategy is changed to AlwaysRevertAll.

Closes-Bug: #1294775

Change-Id: Ia6ef08b6713295c63ce1573017d54727e2c16549

commit_message:
Rename 'AVAILABLE_REGIONS' to 'KEYSTONE_ENDPOINTS'

This should remove a constant source of confusion when dealing with
regions-related issues (since 'AVAILABLE_REGIONS' gets mixed up with
Keystone regions).

Use utils.get_available_keystone_endpoints() method from
openstack_auth, which emits a deprecation notice in case an old
version of setting is used.

DocImpact

Change-Id: I56d95d76f81e1a8d52ee93be0214ff2dd3a709a3
Closes-Bug: #1494251
Depends-On: I482fb71e914131321090d9b2403303c7731e114b

commit_message:
Rename 'AVAILABLE_REGIONS' to 'KEYSTONE_ENDPOINTS'

This should remove a constant source of confusion when dealing with
regions-related issues (since 'AVAILABLE_REGIONS' gets mixed up with
Keystone regions). The legacy name still could be used for indefinite
(as of now) time, but will cause a deprecation warning.

Provide a separate function for getting the actual value and make it
responsible for the deprecation warning.

Change-Id: I482fb71e914131321090d9b2403303c7731e114b
Partial-Bug: #1494251

commit_message:
Added module 8021q at boot in nodes

If module 8021q doesn't loaded, then VLAN mode disabled on network
interfaces. As result network packets don't send/receive via VLANs
between Nodes.

Change-Id: I7d4694ca5c165f2acd9ab5c54d07fad30a13fc60
Closes-Bug: #1525168

commit_message:
Remove argument ServiceLauncher.wait() method

Signature of method wait in ServiceLauncher and ProcessLauncher must
be the same because if user uses service.launch() function and
workers number is taken from config file user couldn't know what
kind of launcher will be instantiated.

commit_message:
Bump version for all library tasks

According to task-based deployment specification
the validator in nailgun checks all tasks version
New deployment engine can be turned on only if all
tasks have version >= 2.0.0
By this commit we confirm that all core tasks have
all dependencies including cross-node and are
ready to work with task-based deployment engine

Closes-Bug:#1528335
Change-Id: I57e52eb8a27bff5a6843c3297a7c97922b49774f

commit_message:
Use temporary yum cache dir during MOS repo sync

During an ISO build, the MOS repository is synced by using reposync
utility. This utility should store cached metadata in a local temporary
directory, in order to prevent issues with stale yum cache.

Change-Id: I92573191f6c9b4d4a17b14890d0ab88ceb0a75c0
Closes-Bug: #1529073

commit_message:
Pass fuel-bootstrap-cli config to containers

* install fuel-bootstrap-cli in mcollective bootstrap
* we need rw permission for successful package
  install\upgrade inside container (linked config file will not be changed -
  new one will be saved with .rpmnew)

Change-Id: I7b2a096cec99ec5923b00f6b084987455adf0637
Closes-Bug: #1528787

[{'number': 6, 'created': '2015-12-22 21:20:54.000000000', 'files': ['cinder/volume/drivers/pure.py', 'releasenotes/notes/pure-enhanced-stats-42a684fe4546d1b1.yaml', 'cinder/tests/unit/test_pure.py'], 'message': 'Enhance the stats reported from the Pure Volume Drivers

This change provides some improvements for older scheduler hints and
stats along with a few new stats that can be used for filtering and
goodness functions. These new stats include:

Latency:
    usec_per_read_op\xa0 - Average arrival-to-completion time, measured in
                        microseconds, for a host read operation.
    usec_per_write_op\xa0- Average arrival-to-completion time, measured in
                        microseconds, for a host write operation.
    queue_depth\xa0      - Average number of queued I/O requests.

IOPS:
    reads_per_sec\xa0 - Number of read requests processed per second.
    writes_per_sec\xa0- Number of write requests processed per second.
                     Bandwidth
    input_per_sec\xa0 - Number of bytes read per second.
    output_per_sec - Number of bytes written per second.

Metadata:
    total_hosts     - Total number of Purity hosts created.
    total_snapshots - Total number of snapshots (includes pending
                      deletion).
    total_pgroups   - Total number of Protection Groups (includes
                      pending deletion).

Note: All of these stats are for the entire array and are not specific
to the Cinder volumes, snapshots, hosts, latency, etc.

As part of the new and improved stats the drivers will respect the
cinder.conf backend “reserved_percentage” option. Previously it was set
to 0.

Last but not least there is a new config option called
“pure_automatic_max_oversubscription_ratio”. This defaults to True, and
when enabled gives the older behavior of automatically calculating the
thin provisioning ratio which was allowed for the backend. If disabled
the driver will now respect the “max_over_subscription_ratio” config
option.

DocImpact
Change-Id: I733f4f90addc39f4c1b720ce63100b15b0523b3e
Implements: blueprint pure-enhanced-stats'}]
commit_message:
Enhance the stats reported from the Pure Volume Drivers

This change provides some improvements for older scheduler hints and
stats along with a few new stats that can be used for filtering and
goodness functions. These new stats include:

Latency:
    usec_per_read_op  - Average arrival-to-completion time, measured in
                        microseconds, for a host read operation.
    usec_per_write_op - Average arrival-to-completion time, measured in
                        microseconds, for a host write operation.
    queue_depth       - Average number of queued I/O requests.

IOPS:
    reads_per_sec  - Number of read requests processed per second.
    writes_per_sec - Number of write requests processed per second.
                     Bandwidth
    input_per_sec  - Number of bytes read per second.
    output_per_sec - Number of bytes written per second.

Metadata:
    total_hosts     - Total number of Purity hosts created.
    total_snapshots - Total number of snapshots (includes pending
                      deletion).
    total_pgroups   - Total number of Protection Groups (includes
                      pending deletion).

Note: All of these stats are for the entire array and are not specific
to the Cinder volumes, snapshots, hosts, latency, etc.

As part of the new and improved stats the drivers will respect the
cinder.conf backend “reserved_percentage” option. Previously it was set
to 0.

Last but not least there is a new config option called
“pure_automatic_max_oversubscription_ratio”. This defaults to True, and
when enabled gives the older behavior of automatically calculating the
thin provisioning ratio which was allowed for the backend. If disabled
the driver will now respect the “max_over_subscription_ratio” config
option.

DocImpact
Change-Id: I733f4f90addc39f4c1b720ce63100b15b0523b3e
Implements: blueprint pure-enhanced-stats

subject: Remove meaningless default value in __get__()
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-12-22 16:41:21.000000000', 'files': ['heat/engine/clients/client_plugin.py'], 'message': 'Remove meaningless default value in __get__()

In function object.__get__(self, instance, owner), owner is always
the owner class, while instance is the instance that the attribute
was accessed through, or None when the attribute is accessed through
the owner. Setting owner default value makes no sense.
refer to:
http://python-reference.readthedocs.org/en/latest/docs/dunderdsc/get.html#get

Change-Id: I2089fd75238e5faefb44ee5125b92f1ee29d8e2d
'}]
commit_message:
Remove meaningless default value in __get__()

In function object.__get__(self, instance, owner), owner is always
the owner class, while instance is the instance that the attribute
was accessed through, or None when the attribute is accessed through
the owner. Setting owner default value makes no sense.
refer to:
http://python-reference.readthedocs.org/en/latest/docs/dunderdsc/get.html#get

Change-Id: I2089fd75238e5faefb44ee5125b92f1ee29d8e2d

commit_message:
Make sure update access mode for volume in available

Cinder only supports update 'read_only' access mode for
volumes which are in available status.
This patch will make sure to update access mode for
volume in available to avoid create/update failed.

Closes-Bug: #1490120

commit_message:
Adding voting Bandit on Bandit gate

This commit adds Bandit gates for Bandit.  This is accomplished
by using the new 'python-jobs-linters' template which calls
'linters' rather than 'pep8'.  A previous Bandit change introduced
the linters target which runs pep8 and bandit-baseline.

Also, add linters to jjb python-jobs job-group so that projects can
easily switch to the linters job.

Change-Id: I360f16077b2fe7d99e5a4c10c2ff57e29af01a03

commit_message:
Eliminate mutable default arguments

The best practice in Python is not to use mutable object (i.e. list,
dictionary, or instances of most classes) as value of default
argument (see https://goo.gl/Kwhg0T). A hacking rule to enforce this 
practice is added as well.

The patch was inspired by CR https://review.openstack.org/#/c/198465/ 
and took most of its code from it as well. That's why original 
copyrights are kept.

Closes-Bug: #1471349
Change-Id: Ia77b1736dbc3d4e28ff2d2c3424e9cfcaefa5077

starting ironic-agent service requires to access
/dev/disk/by-label/ir-vfd-dev which is a soft link to /dev/sdb but
when the ramdisk created with the elements of "ubuntu" and
"ironic-agent" boots, /dev/sdb is not created though this device

commit_message:
mknod virtual floppy disk for ironic-agent

starting ironic-agent service requires to access
/dev/disk/by-label/ir-vfd-dev which is a soft link to /dev/sdb but
when the ramdisk created with the elements of "ubuntu" and
"ironic-agent" boots, /dev/sdb is not created though this device
information exists in /sys filesystem.

Change-Id: Ifa80a460be8cc04d9e4611d0e3874a937c2e39fe
Closes-Bug: #1517814

Allow one AZ has many pods, and each pod is one bottom OpenStack managed
by Tricircle. Tricircle forward regarding request according to the AZ pod
mapping. And one Tenant will be bound to one pod in one AZ, so that

BP: https://blueprints.launchpad.net/tricircle/+spec/implement-stateless

Signed-off-by: Chaoyi Huang <joehuang@huawei.com>
'}]
commit_message:
Create aggregate and az when adding AZ Pod Mapping

Allow one AZ has many pods, and each pod is one bottom OpenStack managed
by Tricircle. Tricircle forward regarding request according to the AZ pod
mapping. And one Tenant will be bound to one pod in one AZ, so that
resources of one tenant will be collocated inside one pod in one AZ.

During the AZ pod mapping creation, also automaticly adding aggregate
and az information according to pod_name(the bottom OpenStack region
name)

BP: https://blueprints.launchpad.net/tricircle/+spec/implement-stateless

Change-Id: I0d60687e36190b279837eba24a3d3c65386ea4c5
Signed-off-by: Chaoyi Huang <joehuang@huawei.com>

commit_message:
Remove cinder API v1 support

This patch removes cinder API v1 support from Cinder, which was deprecated
in Juno in favor of v2 which has been available since Grizzly.

DocImpact
blueprint remove-v1-api
Co-Authored-By: Ivan Kolodyazhny <e0ne@e0ne.info>
Co-Authored-By: Mike Perez <thingee@gmail.com>

Change-Id: Ief7383a1b5da3aad338fbe28b8a409bf831dd894

Change generator config file from tox to oslo-config-generator

download libraries again. In the case that git/pip frequently
timeout, this may cause failure of installation.

commit_message:
Midonet L2 Gateway Management Service plugin

Midonet support for L2 Gateway Management Service.
This patch includes the following:

  * Midonet L2 Gateway Gateway Management Service plugin
  * Unit test for Midonet L2 Gateway Management Service plugin
  * Make a white list of py3.4 unit tests to run because
    l2gw-networking is not py3.4 compatible and should be
    excluded for now.
This patch does not include the following:

  * Add/Delete MAC
  * L2GW update
  * Validations for Gateway Device association
  * Using segmentation_id of l2_gateway

Change-Id: I6213a06752aff03ee1fe2888de2f5fae3e485d0b
Partially Implements: blueprint https://blueprints.launchpad.net/networking-midonet/+spec/l2gw-api-midonet
Co-Authored-By: Ryu Ishimoto <ryu@midokura.com>

subject: Client repr hosts list return value will raise AttributeError: host
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-11-13 04:56:12.000000000', 'files': ['novaclient/tests/unit/fixture_data/hosts.py', 'novaclient/tests/unit/v2/test_hosts.py', 'novaclient/v2/hosts.py'], 'message': 'Client repr hosts list return value will raise AttributeError: host

Hosts list api return body contain host_name key. But host get api
return body contain host key. This will cause host repr function call
raise exception.

We can just add condition statement to determine whether response body
contain host_name attribute. If it is exist then rename it to host.

Change-Id: I38c925739b8bb9ac52eae6ba1ad2e9dec3264832
Closes-Bug: 1515500
'}]
commit_message:
Client repr hosts list return value will raise AttributeError: host

Hosts list api return body contain host_name key. But host get api
return body contain host key. This will cause host repr function call
raise exception.

We can just add condition statement to determine whether response body
contain host_name attribute. If it is exist then rename it to host.

Change-Id: I38c925739b8bb9ac52eae6ba1ad2e9dec3264832
Closes-Bug: 1515500

commit_message:
bay-show doesn't return stack_id

Bay Detail View in magnum-ui wants to link to Stack Detail View in
Orchestration Panel. So, the response of "bay-show" must have
"stack_id".

Change-Id: Icf23688caa1f925ac4cc9e5add527dc1bdaa09a4
Closes-Bug: #1524151

commit_message:
Remove the support for keystone extensions

All keystone extensions have been moved into cores and are
enabled by default, there is no need to configure the extension
in devstack but configure it in devstack will block the
install process.

Change-Id: I7d21b122c641f601295ee7ece3583404b3874dbd
Closes-Bug: #1526033

commit_message:
Put py34 first in the env order of tox

To solve the problem of "db type could not be determined" on py34
we have to run first the py34 env to, then, run py27. This patch
puts py34 first on the tox.ini list of envs to avoid this problem
to happen.

Change-Id: I47cced1e897236740e4069086da10282dd2b1098
Closes-bug: #1489059

subject: Add port 'up' and 'down' notification
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-12-24 12:56:49.000000000', 'files': ['networking_ovn/tests/unit/test_ovn_plugin.py', 'networking_ovn/ovsdb/impl_idl_ovn.py', 'networking_ovn/ovsdb/ovn_nb_notify_handler.py', 'networking_ovn/ovsdb/row_event.py', 'networking_ovn/plugin.py'], 'message': "Add port 'up' and 'down' notification

This patch handles the Logical_Port.up updates.
 - If the Logical_Port.up changes from False to True
   it sets the port status to 'ACTIVE' so that neutron server
   can send 'network-vif-plugged' event to nova.
 - If the Logical_Port.up changes from True to False
   it sets the port status to 'DOWN' so that neutron server
   can send 'network-vif-unplugged' event to nova.

When the port is created, it sets the status to 'DOWN' by default.

All other notify events from ovs idl are ignored.

The credit for this patch goes to Terry Wilson.

(WIP - Test cases)
(Note: ovs.idl.Idl is calling notify 3 times for every Logical_Port.up update.

thrice which in turn is sending the 'network-vif-*' event to nova thrice.
Note sure if this patch should have a work around for this issue)

Co-Authored-By: Terry Wilson <twilson@redhat.com>
Co-Authored-By: Numan Siddique <nusiddiq@redhat.com>

Change-Id: Ieda1a3ce2d612d958283b2e970d8daf0a0f3f18e
Closes-bug: #1457571
"}]
commit_message:
Add port 'up' and 'down' notification

This patch handles the Logical_Port.up updates.
 - If the Logical_Port.up changes from False to True
   it sets the port status to 'ACTIVE' so that neutron server
   can send 'network-vif-plugged' event to nova.
 - If the Logical_Port.up changes from True to False
   it sets the port status to 'DOWN' so that neutron server
   can send 'network-vif-unplugged' event to nova.

When the port is created, it sets the status to 'DOWN' by default.

All other notify events from ovs idl are ignored.

The credit for this patch goes to Terry Wilson.

(WIP - Test cases)
(Note: ovs.idl.Idl is calling notify 3 times for every Logical_Port.up update.
Not sure if ovsdb server is sending the update method
3 times to its clients or not.
Thich is causing the notify function to be called
thrice which in turn is sending the 'network-vif-*' event to nova thrice.
Note sure if this patch should have a work around for this issue)

Co-Authored-By: Terry Wilson <twilson@redhat.com>
Co-Authored-By: Numan Siddique <nusiddiq@redhat.com>

Change-Id: Ieda1a3ce2d612d958283b2e970d8daf0a0f3f18e
Closes-bug: #1457571

commit_message:
Add ability to clear image description

Currently there is no way to clear
image description field. Even if user
left description field empty, it will
not be cleared since empty description
will not be sended to glance.

This fix add to Horizon ability  send
empty description.

Change-Id: I399d3674a2785912f32b7331f3343973199eceaa
Closes-Bug: #1527604

commit_message:
Unify Open vSwitch and Linux Bridge agent configuration file

unifying the Open vSwitch and Linux Bridge agent configuration
file sections and options

Move l2_population, local_ip to Linux Bridge [agent] section,
and replace enable_vxlan in Linux Bridge [agent] section by
tunnel_types.

DocImpact

commit_message:
Fix creating sg rule which ICMP code is not specified validation

When creating security group rule, in that case
where ICMP code is not specified (None) but ICMP type
is specified will not result in an error.

This patch will raise an exception in this situation.

APIImpact
DocImpact

Change-Id: I7c96a2cd0e40098be5def394241600c321bfbd72
Closes-Bug: #1489857

commit_message:
Fix ICMP code value is None in security group rule test

Security group rule with ICMP protocol has type/code value.
In Neutron API, code is specified but type is None or
type is specified but code is None will raise an exception.

This patch modifing ICMP code value which is None to normal.

Closes-Bug: #1490281
Change-Id: Icd9499ea37864a0f68f0af70f9137e8710a3b561

commit_message:
drop use of norm_ns

we shouldn't be modifying id as it makes it very difficult to track
whether it's prefix or not. as the id is not generated by pycadf
it shouldn't be modified by it.

Change-Id: I8de3f83af2446402b003212a2cb71bd40d626d28
Partial-Bug: #1504889
(cherry picked from commit dcd0981d0aa22e552000676879f6849e37c00b74)

subject: Add a 'generate_binary_uuid' helper function
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-12-25 07:20:47.000000000', 'files': ['oslo_utils/uuidutils.py'], 'message': "Add a 'generate_binary_uuid' helper function

The current 'generate_uuid' may return a unicode string
or a binary string depending on which python version it is
being used on. This makes it hard to predict the output
of this function in a way that can be dependened upon to
always be one type, so in at least one place (in a taskflow
review) it is really nice to know and be able to depend on
it being binary, so this adds a function into oslo.utils
to ensure that the uuid returned is a binary string always.

Change-Id: I957c3919fb5754fe3956d8cf7157bb4642a5b30b
"}]
commit_message:
Add a 'generate_binary_uuid' helper function

The current 'generate_uuid' may return a unicode string
or a binary string depending on which python version it is
being used on. This makes it hard to predict the output
of this function in a way that can be dependened upon to
always be one type, so in at least one place (in a taskflow
review) it is really nice to know and be able to depend on
it being binary, so this adds a function into oslo.utils
to ensure that the uuid returned is a binary string always.

Change-Id: I957c3919fb5754fe3956d8cf7157bb4642a5b30b

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-12-26 04:57:54.000000000', 'files': ['senlin/tests/unit/engine/actions/test_action_base.py', 'senlin/engine/actions/base.py'], 'message': "Fix action deserialization

When an action is loaded from database, its dict attributes might be
None. However, the __init__ function will treat such attributes as
assigned, i.e. found in the keyword arguments, so these properties won't

commit_message:
Fix action deserialization

When an action is loaded from database, its dict attributes might be
None. However, the __init__ function will treat such attributes as
assigned, i.e. found in the keyword arguments, so these properties won't
get properly initialized to an empty dict. This patch fix the behavior
by explicitly assigning an empty dict to such properties.

Change-Id: I2e944139e16125c0b4a0cdce94f7a8d3b150ebc8

Currently network plugin imports neutron.db.l3_db, which results
in database model init failure because of some dependency errors.
Since l3 functionality is not implemented yet in network plugin,
remove this import to avoid the failure.

revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2015-12-25 01:35:12.000000000', 'files': ['midonet/neutron/tests/unit/test_extension_vpnaas.py', 'midonet/neutron/services/vpn/service_drivers/midonet_ipsec.py'], 'message': "VPNaaS: Fix the case of multiple ipsec connections

When creating the second ipsec-site-connection on a vpnservice, the
first one is deleted on Neutron DB unintentionally.

Stop updating python db object only for preventing the insertion of

Closes-Bug: #1528417
Change-Id: I12bebbf6d0940a804442b30b3d8fd51bbaf44255
"}]
commit_message:
VPNaaS: Fix the case of multiple ipsec connections

When creating the second ipsec-site-connection on a vpnservice, the
first one is deleted on Neutron DB unintentionally.

Stop updating python db object only for preventing the insertion of
unused dictionary elements so that its update won't be reflected to DB.

Closes-Bug: #1528417
Change-Id: I12bebbf6d0940a804442b30b3d8fd51bbaf44255

commit_message:
Add AZ Pod Mapping and Tenant Pod Bindings

Allow one AZ has many pods, and each pod is one bottom OpenStack managed
by Tricircle. Tricircle forward regarding request according to the AZ pod
mapping. And one Tenant will be bound to one pod in one AZ, so that resources
of one tenant will be collocated inside one pod in one AZ.

BP: https://blueprints.launchpad.net/tricircle/+spec/implement-stateless

Change-Id: Iee9572366539b4263ed7b51cbfe0e9cac1ce795f
Signed-off-by: Chaoyi Huang <joehuang@huawei.com>

commit_message:
ODL internal error with allowed_address_pairs

mac_address needs to be converted into upper case.
ip_address of allowed_address_pairs is actually ip address or netaddress.
(It's very counter-intuitive to the key word, "ip_address")
Always Convert ip address into net address for unified representation.
https://bugs.opendaylight.org/show_bug.cgi?id=4789

Change-Id: I3a4d583d81883cbe42782b68bb1b6c4a0bd3faa3
Signed-off-by: Isaku Yamahata <isaku.yamahata@intel.com>

commit_message:
Reinstate PUBLIC_BRIDGE as a way of adding interface to PUBLIC_BRIDGE

This is a partial revert of the following gerrit:
    https://review.openstack.org/#/c/248835/

With that, we continue to support the usage of PUBLIC_INTERFACE,
so folks that use a local.conf based on Liberty can still use the
old way of adding interface to br-ex.

While the old way will still work, we will keep it undocumented
and display a message to inform user about the expected usage.

Change-Id: I598a3afaa1d5b84fb4707d21bdf406d94aaf0b7f
Signed-off-by: Flavio Fernandes <ffernand@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Catch BackendException during upload image data

Now, when the storage back-end raise BackendException error, Glance
doesn't catch it and raise 500 error. Such as if there is no enough
space for image store, the back-end(Such as Swift) will sometimes
raise a BackendException error.

This patch catch this error when upload image data.

Change-Id: Ib8d120b44a8a4f95bf63449f009145cde891d7c0
Closes-bug: #1529198

commit_message:
Use temporary yum cache dir during MOS repo sync

During an ISO build, the MOS repository is synced by using reposync
utility. This utility should store cached metadata in a local temporary
directory, in order to prevent issues with stale yum cache.

Change-Id: I92573191f6c9b4d4a17b14890d0ab88ceb0a75c0
Closes-Bug: #1529073

commit_message:
Refactoring osbash networking code

In preparation for Liberty, which removes some networks and adds a new
type of network interface configuration (manual), this patch refactors
the osbash networking code.

- fewer hardcoded settings (e.g., removed hardcoded list of networks
  from osbash.sh)

- eliminated code duplication for client-side network configuration and
  split remaining code into separate libraries (functions.ubuntu.sh,
  functions.fedora.sh)

- simplify code, e.g. by removing some magic that deduced network names
  for KVM from variable names like MGMT_NET

- universal functions for reading network and network interface
  configuration into arrays (get_host_network_config,
  get_node_netif_config)

- the number of networks is no longer hardcoded in the template for
  Windows hostnet creation

- renamed some variables, functions and files to (hopefully) be easier
  to understand

Change-Id: Ib0ed26e24d07e093f7a2bf29723b53b558cd769b

commit_message:
Put py34 first in the env order of tox

To solve the problem of "db type could
not be determined" on py34 we have to run first the py34 env to, then, run
py27. This patch puts py34 first on the tox.ini list of envs to avoid this
problem to happen.

Change-Id: I5c838c6f8e9288372ee83cfb993df4e077e75819
Closes-bug: #1489059

commit_message:
Put py34 first in the env order of tox

To solve the problem of "db type could
not be determined" on py34 we have to run first the py34 env to, then, run
py27. This patch puts py34 first on the tox.ini list of envs to avoid this
problem to happen.

Change-Id: I0c6f81154cbd0a2477766c50a4b3d88dc53b668c
Closes-bug: #1489059

commit_message:
EMC VNX: Fix the interface garbage in VNX backend

EMC VNX could not support truly multi-tenancy , so the user will fail to
create multiple network interfaces with the different vlans.
Current VNX Manila driver implementation will leave the interface garbage
in VNX array. So this commit is to remove the garbage interface from VNX.

Change-Id: I1c7dec938e55db264a8dfa42718c75535fe46d5d
Closes-Bug: #1528983

commit_message:
Add tests that constrain db query count

This patch adds unit tests to ML2 and L3 that ensure that the
number of DB calls during list operations for ports, networks,
subnets, routers, and floating IPs remains constant regardless
of the number of ports.

These will prevent changes from slipping in that result in
a separate DB query for each object in a list operation
(for changes to the extensions used by ML2 and the DVR plugin).

Related-Bug: #1525295
Related-Bug: #1513782
Related-Bug: #1525423
Related-Bug: #1525740
Related-Bug: #1526644

Change-Id: I1958fc7c318bbf73238a3ad5be133fa7800c8290

commit_message:

Since oslo-incubator is no longer maintained[1] after
90ae25e38915cc502d9e9c52d59e8fb668a72ae1. And
openstack/common/_i18n.py is not referenced by Manila. Let's remove it.

[1] http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-November/
    079343.html

Closes-Bug: #1529083

commit_message:
Update remotefs driver to use versionedobjects

The following patch updates volume drivers, inherited
from RemoteFSDriver to use modern versionedobjects
instead of dicts.

This patch is relatively huge, but if I split it,
it will be hard to make the whole unit tests passing.

Change-Id: I4b3cf7bf4804daa7baaf21182783a5373054ea04

commit_message:
Remove Nova restriction for vCenter

Currently there are at least two providers for neutron which works with
vCenter: DVS and NSXv. So nova network can't be only one possible solution.

commit_message:
No Mutable Defaults

Do not have mutable defaults in functions/constructors/etc. This
is bad news since they can be changed for the entire run of the
program (and subsequent calls).

Change-Id: I756629a3edca72a4c7fbe748e2f6964a7e827e72

commit_message:

on. Provide a flag for people using simple_logging.

commit_message:
K8s: Remove bay creation functional testing

Remove test case TestBayResource of k8s with(tls_disabled=True) mode.

Bay creation is kinds of wasting time on gate (15 mins), as we have already
TestKubernetesAPIs, in this case, we creat a new bay(tls_disabled=False) to do
API testing, so it will cover TestBayResource case.

P.S. tls_disabled=False will cover tls_disabled=True when do bay creation.
if we want test tls_disabled=True case, better to add new pipe line.

Change-Id: Ie563f1cd526695a943b02749c1bd0734e9380b6d

commit_message:
Scheduler: Move notifier.info to scheduler manager

This patch moves notifer.info from scheduler driver class to manager class,
by doing this, so we don't need to send any notification in drivers.

Besides, this will benifit to outtree drivers.

Closes-Bug: #1483943
Change-Id: I3165024e4735c6e906a21b333a7dc2101ed7e925

commit_message:
Make all repositories independent

  * unite all repos (distro, mos and extra) in one section
  * provide an ability to change all default repos independently
  * change default URL for main mos repo to local one
  * add ability to parse setting.yaml as template
  * (minor) small refactoring to avoid code duplication

Change-Id: I3746d1f8b159c3b92e68682bdaa3e614a425bc70
Closes-Bug: #1525133

commit_message:
Fix gate DSVM tests to make them work

Currently all gate DSVM tests for Zaqar fail. Zaqar's gate_hook function
tries to cd to python-zaqarclient repository directory, but the
directory can't be found. Apparently python-zaqarclient repository
hasn't been cloned.

Seems like the root cause of the problem is recent devstack-gate change:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/234509

Abandoned. Instead created https://review.openstack.org/#/c/261482/
patch for openstack-infra/project-config.

Change-Id: Ie6198fb3375cf6195c7648b93a9b5c11bbdc72b7

commit_message:
Remove Nova restriction for vCenter

Currently there are at least two providers for neutron which works with
vCenter: DVS and NSXv. So nova network can't be only one possible solution.

Change-Id: Ifa485faaa4d3aa1d94298411a088100e3477d68e

Change-Id: Ibdfd4c0989dbda535465e14209dc22cd43c60efa
'}]
commit_message:
[glossary] Unify the deplicated definitions

* "Domain Name Service" and "Domain Name System" to "Domain Name System"
  - mainly use the word "service".
* "ESX" and "ESXi" to "ESX"
  - VMware has recently provided ESXi only.
* "HTTP" and "Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP)" to "HTTP"
* "HTTPS" and "Hypertext Transfer Protocol Secure (HTTPS)" to "HTTPS"

Change-Id: Ibdfd4c0989dbda535465e14209dc22cd43c60efa

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-12-24 16:21:49.000000000', 'files': ['fuelweb_test/helpers/multiple_networks_hacks.py'], 'message': "[stable/8.0]Allow forwarding for non-default admin networks

Since we upgraded master node to CentOS 7 its firewall
blocks all 'FORWARD' traffic by default. Officially Fuel
deals with external DHCP relays while working in multirack
setup, so Internet is supposed to be provided via external
routers too. In the tests we use master node for routing,
so we need to add new accept firewall rules for each rack.
Author: Artem Panchenko
Change-Id: I7fce584cad47c0cc044eeab0372fa8b921cfd3b6
Closes-bug: #1528598
"}]
commit_message:
[stable/8.0]Allow forwarding for non-default admin networks

Since we upgraded master node to CentOS 7 its firewall
blocks all 'FORWARD' traffic by default. Officially Fuel
deals with external DHCP relays while working in multirack
setup, so Internet is supposed to be provided via external
routers too. In the tests we use master node for routing,
so we need to add new accept firewall rules for each rack.
Author: Artem Panchenko
Change-Id: I7fce584cad47c0cc044eeab0372fa8b921cfd3b6
Closes-bug: #1528598

commit_message:
Remove API races from attach and detach methods

This patch uses compare-and-swap to perform atomic DB changes to remove
API races in attach and detach related methods.

Races are removes from the following methods:
- attach
- roll_detaching
- begin_detaching
- unreserve_volume
- reserve_volume

Specs: https://review.openstack.org/232599/

Implements: blueprint cinder-volume-active-active-support
Closes-Bug: #1238093
Change-Id: I646d946209e0921d1056ee89e59b82b814bf9c15

commit_message:
Adjust '410 Gone' exception in service broker negative tests

Tempest-lib 0.12.0 contains necessary code for checking correct exception.
This patch replaces 'UnexpectedResponceCode' exception to correct 'Gone' exception.

Aslo, this patch add expectedFail for negative test.

Change-Id: Ib460b6fc495060a1bd6dd7d0443ff983f8e9f06b
Related-Bug: #1527949

commit_message:
Allow to make operations on a given cluster

Add parameter (`cluster_id`) to the appropriate methods to make
possible to perform operations (such as launch deployment, reset
environment etc) on a given cluster.

Change-Id: I6cc80335cbcdaa11be57e6cfc61ea579a39ac90e
Closes-Bug: #1398043

commit_message:
Put py34 first in the env order of tox

To solve the problem of "db type could
not be determined" on py34 we have to run first the py34 env to, then, run
py27. This patch puts py34 first on the tox.ini list of envs to avoid this
problem to happen.

Change-Id: Ic0d3a5ba6edd4f62af612683fefcaf2655da0fb5
Closes-bug: #1489059

commit_message:
Replace tenant_id with project_id in auth_utils

The 'tenant_id' passing to keystoneclient.v3.client.Client is
deprecated, and may be removed in the 2.0.0 release[1]. Replace
it with 'project_id' as suggested.

[1]:
https://github.com/openstack/python-keystoneclient/blob/f8c47a1aa0c12e2fb374e66f8787287069acbdd9/keystoneclient/v3/client.py#L73

commit_message:
Make all repositories independent

  * unite all repos (distro, mos and extra) in one section
  * provide an ability to change all default repos independently
  * change default URL for main mos repo to local one
  * add ability to parse setting.yaml as template
  * (minor) small refactoring to avoid code duplication

commit_message:
Bump Ironic ref to 7.0.0-rc2

Currently during executing Ironic manifests on non-primary
controllers after installing main ironic-common package it notifies
db sync from db/sync class, which are not in catalog. And as a result
we have resource not found error. Upstream patch [1] fixes this problem
and we need to update ref on top.

[1] I29939384bf96b82d9124307222a239b8aa95336b

commit_message:
Bump Ironic ref to 7.0.0-rc2

Currently during executing Ironic manifests on non-primary
controllers after installing main ironic-common package it notifies
db sync from db/sync class, which are not in catalog. And as a result
we have resource not found error. Upstream patch [1] fixes this problem
and we need to update ref on top.

[1] I29939384bf96b82d9124307222a239b8aa95336b

Change-Id: Ia9b17e84e7747e069a679649a1f35ebad8614b79
Closes-bug: #1529046

commit_message:
Make v3 update_role use **kwargs & doc string

As we discussed on
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2015-July/068864.html
All http POST/PUT methods need to contain **kwargs as their arguments.

This patch makes update_role of v3 identity_client use **kwargs.
Also update doc string for the same.

Partially implements blueprint consistent-service-method-names

Change-Id: Ic30ce16d5240e597b5abab1590fbfa251321f2b1

commit_message:
Clean-up code

1. Typos
2. Unused variables
3. Shadowed built-ins not in API
4. New line before binary operations
5. Redundant parenthesis
6. Single quoted docstring
7. super().__init__()

Change-Id: Ib8c66086cfdcba34c17a662454969a6b95706b5b

commit_message:
Add Support for json-home content_type in wsgi

JSON-Home data will be published when request has content_type
as application/json-home.

This patch add support of json-home as supproted content_type in wsgi.

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-json-home

Change-Id: I1ee4491bf16dbbd716ef6fd00468d376f18eaffa

Add resource_template_with_parent JSON-Home methods

This patch adds base methods for resource_template_with_parent
to generate JSON-Home document.

This will be used to generate below JSON-Home doc-

Deploy stateless Tricircle in one node using DevStack. Script
starts an extra Neutron server for bottom region, and updates

commit_message:
Script to deploy stateless Tricircle

Deploy stateless Tricircle in one node using DevStack. Script
starts an extra Neutron server for bottom region, and updates
Keystone endpoint to move original Nova service to bottom region
as well as to register Tricircle Nova gateway as compute service
in top region.

This patch also updates readme file to introduce stateless
Tricircle depolyment.

Change-Id: I5c63d96bf2f7c93cc8ff56388f805425347bd8ea

commit_message:
Make all repositories independent

  * unite all repos (distro, mos and extra) in one section
  * provide an ability to change all default repos independently
  * change default URL for main mos repo to local one
  * add ability to parse setting.yaml as template
  * (minor) small refactoring to avoid code duplication

Change-Id: I3746d1f8b159c3b92e68682bdaa3e614a425bc70
Closes-Bug: #1525133

server, which would lead to exceptions when

commit_message:
Create own script for running the dsvm gate

In order to fix the gate properly we need some control over the way
we setup the environment.

This patch creates a `tools\post_test_hook.sh` file that for now mirrors
the one stated in openstack-infra/project-config.

Later the project-config will be modified to use it. After that we can
start configuring the environment to our needs.

Change-Id: Ib9388e7f5001d7efa35f6f16421251c9a59ad396
Partial-Bug: #1492942

commit_message:
Support standard Manila capability flags in NetApp cDOT driver

With the addition of capability lists in the CapabilitiesFilter, we
can now support the standard values of compression, dedupe, and
thin_provisioning in the NetApp cDOT driver. The legacy scoped
values continue to be supported (i.e. netapp:compression, etc.).

Closes-Bug: #1493951
Change-Id: I39099b5e8bfeb03d805d566e787b6c4c5d6221e1

subject: nova::compute: remove nova::vncproxy::common class
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-12-08 16:09:43.000000000', 'files': ['manifests/compute.pp'], 'message': 'nova::compute: remove nova::vncproxy::common class

nova::vncproxy::common depends on parameters from both nova::compute and
nova::vncproxy, but both nova::compute and nova::vncproxy include
nova::vncproxy::common. This is not a good practice with Puppet 3, and
forms a reference circle that cannot be solved with Puppet 4. It would
be better for the user to include nova::vncproxy afterhead themselves,
which will include nova::vncproxy::common anyway.

Change-Id: Ied06f5f5796f41b115c19731799c8cc992d4148d
'}]
commit_message:
nova::compute: remove nova::vncproxy::common class

nova::vncproxy::common depends on parameters from both nova::compute and
nova::vncproxy, but both nova::compute and nova::vncproxy include
nova::vncproxy::common. This is not a good practice with Puppet 3, and
forms a reference circle that cannot be solved with Puppet 4. It would
be better for the user to include nova::vncproxy afterhead themselves,
which will include nova::vncproxy::common anyway.

Change-Id: Ied06f5f5796f41b115c19731799c8cc992d4148d

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-12-24 05:54:04.000000000', 'files': ['setup.cfg'], 'message': "Remove py26 support

as of mitaka, the infra team won't have the resources available to
reasonably test py26, also the oslo team is dropping py26 support
from their libraries. sine we rely on oslo for a lot of our work,
and depend on infra for our CI, we should drop py26 support too.

Change-Id: I05a083458041146178894dda7e444a1e1978bf79
Closes-Bug: 1519510
"}]
commit_message:
Remove py26 support

as of mitaka, the infra team won't have the resources available to
reasonably test py26, also the oslo team is dropping py26 support
from their libraries. sine we rely on oslo for a lot of our work,
and depend on infra for our CI, we should drop py26 support too.

Change-Id: I05a083458041146178894dda7e444a1e1978bf79
Closes-Bug: 1519510
